'''Helga Gitmark''' ([[30 September]] [[1929]] - [[2 August]] [[2008]]) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] politician for the [[Centre Party (Norway)|Centre Party]].

She was the [[Minister of the Environment (Norway)|Minister of the Environment]] from March to October 1973 during the [[cabinet Korvald]], replacing [[Trygve Haugeland]]. She lost this job when the cabinet Korvald fell.

She served in the position of deputy representative to the [[Stortinget|Norwegian Parliament]] from [[Aust-Agder]] during the term 1977&ndash;1981. On the local level she was member of [[Lillesand]] [[municipal council (Norway)|municipal council]] during the terms 1971&ndash;1975 and 1991&ndash;1995. She was born in [[Holt, Norway|Holt]].

She was a member of the central committee of the Centre Party from 1969 to 1979, and was deputy party leader from 1973 to 1979.

In addition she was a member of the board in several organizations within the [[Church of Norway]], including the [[Diocese of Agder|Diocese Council of Agder]], as well as other Christian organizations.

